		{
			"id":"f79e09e0077a9331",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# INSPO",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-2440,
			"y":-1140,
			"width":260,
			"height":60
		},
		{
			"id":"a2769915cb2fd582",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Login n Sign-Up Screen",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-3148,
			"y":-1158,
			"width":440,
			"height":100
		},
		{"id":"b7667c0df10e3c87","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621144117.png","x":3556,"y":-1642,"width":903,"height":566},
		{"id":"fc62416f002ce760","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260620115542.png","x":-1220,"y":860,"width":1481,"height":753},
		{"id":"7621ef40055a8b18","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621123122.png","x":2380,"y":-1642,"width":999,"height":624},
		{"id":"6f0788ce9405f32f","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621145410.png","x":2840,"y":1020,"width":176,"height":400},
		{"id":"ad51ead56c69c0d8","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621145547.png","x":3100,"y":1020,"width":176,"height":399},
		{"id":"4086d9f41b1ce1a0","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621145558.png","x":3320,"y":1060,"width":176,"height":400},
		{"id":"42d68b22c3f35e2b","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621144431.png","x":4560,"y":-1640,"width":999,"height":622},
		{"id":"28f1a61bac47830e","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621143425.png","x":4560,"y":-2437,"width":999,"height":625},
		{
			"id":"89b88bf4f54971e1",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Form Width Is Intentionally Small\n\nNotice most forms are narrow.\n\nThis is not aesthetic.\n\nWide forms create:\n\n```\nlong eye travellarge visual footprinthigher perceived complexity\n```\n\nNarrow forms create:\n\n```\nquick scanningshorter eye movementsfaster completion\n```\n\nHuman brains estimate effort visually before reading.\n\nA narrow form literally feels easier.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":2860,
			"y":-840,
			"width":660,
			"height":560
		},
		{
			"id":"aba4323ff9e61dd7",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# The Invisible Question\n\nEvery signup page is answering:\n\n```\nWhy should I create an account?\n```\n\nbefore asking:\n\n```\nCreate an account\n```\n\nLook carefully.\n\nEvery example has value communication:\n\n- CRM talks about growth\n- Peerlist talks about professional network\n- PeopleGPT shows social proof\n- Resume shows outcomes\n\nBecause signup is fundamentally a sales problem.\n\nNot a UI problem.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":4380,
			"y":-480,
			"width":620,
			"height":560
		},
		{
			"id":"fa841de77acadaa5",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Pattern 1  Progressive Commitment\n\nNotice how the simplest page is:\n\n- logo\n- email field\n- continue\n\nNo password.  \nNo name.  \nNo phone.\n\nThis isn't laziness.\n\nThis is commitment architecture.\n\nThe brain evaluates:\n\n```\n1 field = easy7 fields = work\n```\n\nEven if both ultimately require the same information.\n\nDesigners call this:\n\n**Perceived Effort Reduction**\n\nThe user mentally says:\n\n> \"Sure, I can enter an email.\"\n\nOnly after commitment begins do you ask for more.\n\n---",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":1520,
			"y":-2480,
			"width":320,
			"height":780
		},
		{
			"id":"e1c8eda1297ed98b",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Signup Pages Borrow Trust\n\nLook closely.\n\nPeopleGPT:\n\n- logos\n- testimonials\n- badges\n\nResume:\n\n- companies\n- statistics\n- founder quote\n\nPeerlist:\n\n- users already inside\n\nThe page is essentially saying:\n\n```\nDon't trust us.Trust everyone already using us.\n```\n\nThis is called:\n\n**Borrowed Trust**",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":6080,
			"y":-1280,
			"width":560,
			"height":720
		},
		{
			"id":"af91739f1e999b6c",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Social Proof Is Positioned Near Decision Points\n\nNotice where proof appears.\n\nNot at the top.\n\nNot hidden.\n\nUsually:\n\n```\nnear buttonnear formnear CTA\n```\n\nReason:\n\nTrust decays.\n\nThe user needs reassurance exactly when uncertainty peaks.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":5360,
			"y":-440,
			"width":540,
			"height":600
		},
		{"id":"b0f9528d586c83e2","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621124417.png","x":3459,"y":-2600,"width":1000,"height":626},
		{
			"id":"59c17243560f6852",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"#  Good Signup Pages Reduce Future Anxiety\n\nLook at wording.\n\nBad wording:\n\n```\nCreate account\n```\n\nGood wording:\n\n```\nStart free trialContinueJoin cohortExplore\n```\n\nThe subtle message:\n\n```\nYou aren't marrying us.You're trying us.\n```\n\nDesigners reduce future commitment fear.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-4880,
			"y":-1280,
			"width":712,
			"height":520
		},
		{
			"id":"f9a8caffe0ada60d",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Most Pages Have One Visual Gravity Center\n\nYour eyes are pulled somewhere.\n\nUsually:\n\n```\nheadlineformillustration\n```\n\nNot all three equally.\n\nOne dominates.\n\nThe others support.\n\nGood pages have hierarchy.\n\nBad pages have competition.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-4293,
			"y":-590,
			"width":432,
			"height":560
		},
		{
			"id":"56897bddd0185c3f",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# ==Signup Screens Are Actually Risk Screens==\n\nThe user's hidden questions:\n\n```\nWill this waste my time?Will they spam me?Will I regret this?Will this be useful?Can I leave later?\n```\n\nThe best signup pages answer those questions without explicitly saying them",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-3725,
			"y":-102,
			"width":420,
			"height":460
		},
		{
			"id":"db5894a3f112dac2",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# White Space Is Doing Psychological Work\n\nHuge empty regions exist.\n\nNot because designers had nothing to add.\n\nBecause signup is a single-task screen.\n\nEvery extra element creates:\n\n```\ndecision branchesattention forkscognitive load\n```\n\nVeterans aggressively remove options.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":3400,
			"y":-4480,
			"width":530,
			"height":500
		},
		{
			"id":"1d141b9562d33bac",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# ==The highest-leverage insight for SideQuestHQ==\n\nA veteran UX designer would likely conclude:\n\n**The first signup screen should not start with account creation.**\n\nIt should start with identity and intent.\n\nNot:\n\n```\nEmailPasswordCreate account\n```\n\nBut:\n\n```\nWhat do you want to finish learning?\n```\n\nBecause your product promise is not:\n\n> Create an account.\n\nYour product promise is:\n\n> Continue the thing you keep postponing.\n\nThe moment a user types:\n\n```\nMachine Learning Playlist\nGerman\nPsychology\nSystem Design\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-2480,
			"y":-720,
			"width":520,
			"height":760
		},
		{
			"id":"c4edcc510d2a51d1",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# ==Labels Above Fields Are Disappearing==\n\n==Many modern forms rely heavily on placeholders.==\n\nThis isn't always better UX.\n\nBut it reveals something:\n\nDesigners are trying to reduce visual density.\n\nThey're trading explicitness for simplicity.\n\nVeterans know:\n\n```\nLow frictionvsHigh clarity\n```\n\nis a constant tradeoff.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-2740,
			"y":160,
			"width":520,
			"height":472
		},
		{
			"id":"3e6e48cdb5d1d543",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# ==The Screen Is Split Into Two Brains==\n\nAll three examples use:\n\n```\nLeft Side  = Emotional Brain\nRight Side = Rational Brain\n```\n\nor vice versa.\n\nThe form exists for the rational brain.\n\nThe marketing panel exists for the emotional brain.\n\n---\n\nTraditional signup:\n\n```\n[ Form ]\n```\n\nSplit-screen signup:\n\n```\n[ Why this matters ] [ Do the thing ]\n```\n\nHuge difference.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-5171,
			"y":-4760,
			"width":500,
			"height":680
		},
		{
			"id":"e564b6ef4cba61ff",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# They're Fighting Form Blindness\n\nPeople have seen signup forms 10,000 times.\n\nTheir brain automatically categorizes:\n\n```\nName\nEmail\nPassword\n```\n\nas administrative work.\n\nThe marketing panel interrupts that autopilot.\n\nIt reminds the user:\n\n```\nThis is not paperwork.\nThis is access.\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-5457,
			"y":-666,
			"width":520,
			"height":564
		},
		{
			"id":"50bab79fa0cdc2ee",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# The Left Panel Is A Psychological Preview\n\nRemote does this particularly well.\n\nNotice the mini UI mockups.\n\nThose aren't screenshots.\n\nThey're future memories.\n\nThe page is showing:\n\n```\nAfter signup...this is what life looks like.\n```\n\nThe brain loves previews.\n\nUncertainty drops.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-4281,
			"y":-4760,
			"width":549,
			"height":480
		}
	],
